Dead by Daylight-playing as a killer, I can't catch survivors, and playing as a survivor, I can't escape from a killer. True story and pretty good work so far.

In General, quite an interesting game, although at first it may seem monotonous. But it's not, because every time you load up on the rink, you still don't know what's waiting for you-a great farm and a promotion or the Hellfire of your chair. A variety of emotions you just provided. Of the minuses it is worth noting that small bugs, but this is a feature of the game.

